[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating dynamic access classes**\n\nI need to think about whether nested helper classes fall under dynamic-access classes and if they're considered one-to-one mapping. The primary dynamic access class is org.jboss...ResteasyDeploymentImpl. It seems that while runtime will reflectively access helper classes using loadClass and newInstance, the dynamic access coverage report might only track call sites in the active class, not the helpers. I also wonder if there’s a potential checkstyle issue with having `throws Exception` in a placeholder.\n\n**Evaluating code improvements**\n\nI'm considering whether to add a license header to the new file. I think it’s a yes. I wonder if I could enhance assertions and type annotations in Java, particularly with some variables like `ResteasyDeploymentImpl deployment` and `Object defaultContextObject`. Also, using the markdown style for comments could be better, though there are no comments currently. I see potential issues with `DefaultContextContract` as it has an empty body. I also want to look into `JndiComponentResourceFactory.registered` and its possible effects on `InitialContext`. I'll inspect the source further.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_073818f911defdc20169fe2ded7368819eafc836ada4e3bd5b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp_i3596l7xyQ1D57arujF1hKAzXclre-PTqOaL_wVXEuWEPo-RhS0M0LUY7NsYQawp3Ly-f9ti5uZvbgMCr-v6Rij8eZHvlBUqtEVO0frdDr2kASNTLzLRqgBhNe8Z2Qj7ll0Jj6l8AARo0Pore0vg3a6r0sfYNWnH0U2jN4N7V3GLxmU0V1PXZ0oVSHBnzuPTp3Zx9aPYAZheafYcYT1rPIA_JIg2qQBZ3aJvovyobacogE483FDwcmhFyk_AlkXyArmSL7GZNl2IctNQCRiGPH8rHbHNSwayQsRd5nLh-diLxqKrDoBlaVG954dseoqQwpd9W8tL6SDQ2XKg0wZvhRiV8XPdhZItHm4i2WewUR5h6VFIaecFKV0Fj15rWHjMvvl0hiVzIEWOQppcRKBPgh9B2pW9rjKusNEF2oJ6YOp13tnMUUjnpS6VcXewlxXbXimslTHmsUq6un9t53-nKpT0e2vLj7qA_PMMMsJ43YhpN3bWtZRfOrELp0PJ1Lmo5aeAJZFSVm3r51p2xCRiW3MdOFrtsrQRfvUxyKMgCkUiGtDu1c5E84iXSj